          "description": "Step 4 says 'If split verdicts persist and arbitration is still available, use at most one arbitration round' but does not define when split verdicts count as persisting — after one revision attempt, after one full round, or another criterion",
          "source_section": "<steps> Step 4"
        }
      ],
      "redesign_guidance": "Specify the trigger explicitly, e.g., 'If a revision round still yields split verdicts (at least one reviewer rejecting or materially pushing back after the leader revises) and arbitration has not yet been used, apply one arbitration round.'"
